      "content": "It's understandable to want to ease the burden on your loved ones, but it's also important to consider your own needs. You can't pour from an empty cup. If you feel like you're taking up too much space in their lives, maybe it's time to reevaluate your own coping strategies. You don't have to carry the weight alone. Seeking help for yourself can also be a way to support them, not just from a distance. Remember, taking care of yourself isn't selfish—it allows you to be there for others in a healthy way.",
      "source": "target",
